==History==

===Thalidomide===
{{further|Thalidomide}}
[[Thalidomide]] was originally developed and prescribed as a cure for morning sickness in [[West Germany]], but its use was discontinued when it was found to cause [[congenital disorder|birth defect]]s. The [[United States]] [[Food and Drug Administration]] never approved thalidomide for use as a cure for morning sickness.

